If Law and Custom be really at variance, (which is hardly the case here,) Custom must yield to Law, not Law to Custom.

We ask them, thirdly: Do they seriously think that a man who takes an ordinary meal kneeling, necessarily commits a sin? If they assert this, since all sin is a transgression of a divine law, I ask what law he transgresses? If they grant that there is no sin in this, whence arises the sin of the same posture in the Lord’s Supper?
